      <h2 id="what-are-cookies">What are cookies?</h2>

      <p>Cookies are small text files that websites store in your browser. They are commonly used to remember preferences, track sessions, and serve targeted advertising. Many news sites use dozens of cookies from advertising networks and data brokers.</p>

      <h2 id="our-approach">Our approach</h2>

      <p>{{ site.title }} does not set any first-party cookies. We made a deliberate decision to avoid them entirely.</p>

      <p>Instead of cookies, we use your browser's <strong>localStorage</strong> to save your preferences and reading data. localStorage is different from cookies in important ways:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>It is never sent to our server, it stays entirely on your device</li>
        <li>It cannot be used to track you across websites</li>
        <li>It is not accessible to third parties</li>
        <li>You can view, export, and delete it at any time from the <a href="/your-data/">Your Data</a> page</li>
      </ul>

